]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"01bf0d",
"children":[
"The two most common ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"gastrointestinal",
"children":[
"GI"
]
},
" ischemic disorders are acute mesenteric ischemia (AMI) and colonic ischemia."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e4ab88",
"children":[
"Causes include cardiogenic emboli, thrombosis, and low flow states owing to hypotension or vasoactive drugs. In ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"acute mesenteric ischemia",
"children":[
"AMI"
]
},
","
]
},
" leukocytosis, hemoconcentration, increased anion gap metabolic acidosis, and elevations in ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"lactate dehydrogenase",
"children":[
"LDH"
]
},
" and/or amylase levels are seen."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
